%% Git Basic Workflow Diagram
%% Shows: init → add → commit → push cycle

graph TB
    Start([Start New Project]) --> Init[git init]
    Init --> |Creates .git folder| Working[Working Directory]
    
    Working --> |Make changes| Files[Edit Files]
    Files --> Add[git add .]
    Add --> |Files moved to| Staging[Staging Area]
    
    Staging --> Commit[git commit -m 'message']
    Commit --> |Saved to| Local[Local Repository]
    
    Local --> Push[git push origin main]
    Push --> |Uploaded to| Remote[GitHub Repository]
    
    Remote --> |Others can| Clone[git clone]
    Clone --> |Download to| Working2[Their Working Directory]
    
    Remote --> |Get updates| Pull[git pull]
    Pull --> Working
    
    style Start fill:#e1f5ff
    style Init fill:#fff3e0
    style Add fill:#fff3e0
    style Commit fill:#fff3e0
    style Push fill:#fff3e0
    style Working fill:#f0f7ff
    style Staging fill:#fff9e6
    style Local fill:#e8f5e9
    style Remote fill:#fce4ec
    style Working2 fill:#f0f7ff
    style Clone fill:#fff3e0
    style Pull fill:#fff3e0

